&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Coordinator – Urgent and Emergency Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Project Co-ordinator to provide support to the team in delivering the high-profile Urgent and Emergency Care, Better Care Fund and Ageing Well programmes. This will involve a broad range of activities to include event planning, developing new tools and data analysis, all of which will utilise your excellent communication and organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supporting a team of project / programme managers working across a number of disciplines supporting our systems and organisations across the South East to transform patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be passionate about making a difference and be agile and adaptable to change. Being able to plan and manage priorities in order to meet deadlines is essential and your skills in analysing, interpreting and summarising information will be key to this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held w/c 30th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKeith HardyJob titleHead of Urgent and Emergency Care TransformationEmail addresskeith.hardy@nhs.netTelephone number07730 381298&lt;/p&gt;
